                    "text": "<h3><strong>RETURNS AND WARRANTY</strong></h3><p>We want you to love your Bonds Creek knife. If for <em>any reason</em> you’re not satisfied with your purchase, contact us within <strong>30 days</strong> of delivery and we’ll help make it right. This includes:</p><ul><li>Assistance with fit, finish, or usage questions</li><li>Options for exchange or store credit<br/>(<em>Note:</em> This period applies to unused knives returned in original condition — see <em>Returns</em> below.)</li></ul><h3><strong>2. Returns (Buyer’s Remorse / Unused Products)</strong></h3><p>We accept returns of unused knives within <strong>30 days</strong> of purchase for a <strong>refund or exchange</strong>.<br/>To qualify:</p><ul><li>Knife must be in <em>new, un-used condition</em></li><li>Original packaging, sheath, and all included accessories must be returned</li><li>Customer is responsible for return shipping</li></ul><p>To start a return:</p><ol><li>Contact support at <a><strong>BondsCreekKnives@gmail.com</strong></a></li><li>We’ll issue a return authorization and return shipping instructions</li><li>Once received and inspected, refunds will be issued to the original payment method</li></ol><p><em>Used knives or items not in original condition may not qualify for refund.</em></p><h3><strong>3. Lifetime Warranty (“Bonds Creek Promise”)</strong></h3><p>Every Bonds Creek knife is backed by our <strong>Lifetime Warranty</strong> against <em>defects in materials and craftsmanship</em>. This means:</p><ul><li>We guarantee your blade will perform as intended</li><li>If a manufacturing defect arises, we’ll repair or replace the knife at our discretion</li><li>Warranty is valid for the <em>original purchaser</em> only</li></ul><p>This warranty <strong>does not cover</strong>:</p><ul><li>Normal wear from use (e.g., dulling of the edge)</li><li>Damage due to misuse, abuse, or improper maintenance</li><li>Modifications or alterations made outside our workshop</li><li>Loss, theft, or cosmetic wear that does not affect function</li></ul><p>To file a warranty claim:</p><ol><li>Email <a><strong>BondsCreekKnives@gmail.com</strong></a> with photos and a description of issue</li><li>We’ll provide instructions on how to send the knife in for evaluation</li><li>After evaluation, we’ll repair or replace the knife and return it to you</li></ol><p>We may:</p><ul><li>Sharpen, rewrap handles, or refurbish surfaces</li><li>Replace components or entire knife if necessary<br/></li></ul><h3><strong>4. Generational Service & Sharpening</strong></h3><p>Like the best American-made knife brands, we offer ongoing service to keep your blade going strong. Under our <strong>Bonds Creek Promise</strong>:</p><ul><li>We <em>will</em> sharpen, service, and maintain your Bonds Creek knife for life</li><li>You can send it back anytime for edge restoration or maintenance (return shipping may apply)</li></ul><p><br/></p><h3><strong>5. How to Ship a Knife to Us</strong></h3><ul><li>Package your knife safely — blade covered and secure</li><li>Include your <strong>order number</strong>, contact info, and reason for service/return</li><li>Use a trackable shipping method — we aren’t responsible for items lost in transit</li></ul><p>Shipping address will be provided after you contact support.</p><h3><strong>6. Questions?</strong></h3><p>If anything is unclear or you want help before returning your knife, we’re here to help.<br/><a><strong>BondsCreekKnives@gmail.com</strong></a><br/>We’re committed to knives that work as hard as you do.</p>",
